extends ../layout

block header
  meta(name="description", content="Tools I like to use.")
  title Tools

block content
  section
    h1 Tools
    p.
      This is a list of tools I like. Most of them are CLI-based.

  section
    h2 Current Tools
    p Tools I currently use.
    .push
      div.
        #[a(href="https://github.com/ggreer/the_silver_searcher") ag] - A wicked
        fast source code search tool.
      div.
        #[a(href="http://cscope.sourceforge.net/") Cscope] - A code search tool
        for C and other languages
      div.
        #[a(href="https://github.com/adamheins/f") f] - A tool for favouriting
        files, directories, and git branches.
      div.
        #[a(href="https://github.com/junegunn/fzf") fzf] - A fuzzy-finder for
        the command line.
      div.
        #[a(href="http://brew.sh/") Homebrew] - A package manager for OSX.
      div.
        #[a(href="https://mosh.mit.edu/") mosh] - A more robust replacement for
        ssh.
      div.
        #[a(href="http://www.passwordstore.org/") pass] - A local password
        manager based on gpg.
      div.
        #[a(href="http://www.vim.org/") vim] - An excellent text editor.
      div.
        #[a(href="http://www.vimperator.org/vimperator") Vimperator] - An
        add-on for Firefox that makes it look and behave similar to vim.
      div.
        #[a(href="https://github.com/rupa/z") z] - Learns which directories you
        visit most and takes you there based on a regex.
      div.
        #[a(href="http://www.zsh.org/") zsh] - The shell I currently use.
        Mostly compatible with bash and more refined.

  section
    h2 Prospective Tools
    p.
      These are tools that I am interested in using once the projects are more
      mature.
    .push
      div.
        #[a(href="https://neovim.io/") neovim] - A rewrite of vim to strip out
        the cruft and add some much needed features. Currently lacks full lua
        support, so it breaks some plugins.

  section
    h2 Vim Plugins
    p.
      Some of the plugins I use for vim. For the full list, look in my
      #[a(href="https://github.com/adamheins/.vim/tree/master/bundle") ~/.vim/bundle]
      directory.
    .push
      div.
        #[a(href="http://www.vim.org/scripts/script.php?script_id=31") a] -
        Toggles between C header (.h) and source (.c) files.
      div.
        #[a(href="https://github.com/airblade/vim-gitgutter") gitgutter] - Shows
        a git diff in the page gutter.
      div.
        #[a(href="https://github.com/ntpeters/vim-better-whitespace") better-whitespace]
        - Highlights trailing whitespace and makes it easy to remove.
      div.
        #[a(href="http://cscope.sourceforge.net/cscope_vim_tutorial.html") Cscope]
        - A plugin for the code search tool mentioned above.
      div.
        #[a(href="https://github.com/kien/ctrlp.vim") ctrlp] - File search plugin.
      div.
        #[a(href="https://github.com/Shougo/neocomplete.vim") neocomplete] -
        Autocompletion engine that is very easy to set up.
      div.
        #[a(href="https://github.com/scrooloose/nerdtree") NERDTree] - Nice
        directory browsing.
      div.
        #[a(href="https://github.com/jeffkreeftmeijer/vim-numbertoggle") numbertoggle]
        - Toggle line numbers between absolute and relative mode.
      div.
        #[a(href="https://github.com/vim-scripts/tComment") tComment] -
        Provides shortcuts for commenting out blocks of code.
